-- Princeton Names Economist Lee as Provost to Succeed Eisgruber
-- B y   O l i v e r   S t a l e y
-- 2013-06-05T14:30:11Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-06-05/princeton-names-economist-lee-as-provost-to-succeed-eisgruber.html
Princeton University named  David S. Lee , a professor of economics and public affairs, as its next
provost.  Lee, who is director of Princeton’s Industrial Relations
Section, will succeed  Christopher Eisgruber , who will become
president July 1, the university in Princeton, New Jersey, said
today in a  statement  on its website. Eisgruber is replacing
 Shirley Tilghman , who served as president from 2001.  As provost, Lee will be Princeton’s chief academic and
budgetary officer, with responsibility for the university’s
long-range planning. Lee attended Harvard University as an
undergraduate and received his master’s and Ph.D. degrees from
Princeton, where he has taught since 2007.  Former Princeton provosts include  Amy Gutmann , president of
the University of Pennsylvania, and  Neil Rudenstine , former
president of Harvard.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Oliver Staley  in London at 
 ostaley@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
